# 📊 Model Results

This directory contains the training outputs, evaluation metrics, dataset visualizations, and prediction samples generated during the development of the **Real-Time Helmet Detection System using YOLOv8**.

---

## 🎯 Objective

The goal of this project is to automatically detect whether a rider is wearing a helmet or not using a deep learning-based object detection model trained on annotated rider images.

---

## 📁 Folder Contents

| File                          | Description                                       |
| ----------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
| `results.png`                 | Training and validation metrics across epochs     |
| `PR_curve.png`                | Precision-Recall Curve                            |
| `F1_curve.png`                | F1 Score vs Confidence Threshold                  |
| `confusion_matrix.png`        | Classification performance visualization          |
| `train_batch_sample.jpg`      | Annotated training dataset samples                |
| `validation_batch_sample.jpg` | Annotated validation dataset samples              |
| `sample_predictions/`         | Example detections generated by the trained model |

---

## 🖼️ Dataset Visualization

### Training Dataset Samples

The image below shows annotated samples from the training dataset used during model development.

![Training Dataset](train_batch_sample.jpg)

---

### Validation Dataset Samples

The validation dataset was used to evaluate model performance on unseen images.

![Validation Dataset](validation_batch_sample.jpg)

---

## 📈 Performance Metrics

The model was evaluated using standard object detection metrics.

| Metric              | Score |
| ------------------- | ----- |
| AP (With Helmet)    | 0.877 |
| AP (Without Helmet) | 0.654 |
| mAP@0.5             | 0.765 |

---

## 📉 Precision-Recall Curve

The Precision-Recall Curve illustrates the trade-off between precision and recall across different confidence thresholds.

![PR Curve](PR_curve.png)

A larger area under the curve indicates stronger detection performance.

---

## 📊 F1 Score Curve

The F1 Score combines precision and recall into a single metric and helps identify the optimal confidence threshold.

![F1 Curve](F1_curve.png)

---

## 🔍 Confusion Matrix

The confusion matrix provides insight into the model's classification behavior by highlighting correct predictions and misclassifications.

![Confusion Matrix](confusion_matrix.png)

---

## 🚀 Key Observations

* Strong performance in detecting riders wearing helmets.
* Reliable detection across different viewpoints and riding conditions.
* Performance decreases in heavily occluded scenes and low-resolution images.
* The model demonstrates good generalization on unseen validation data.

---

## 🏍️ Sample Predictions

Example prediction outputs generated by the trained YOLOv8 model are available in the `sample_predictions` directory.

These examples demonstrate:

* Helmet detection
* No-helmet detection
* Bounding box localization
* Confidence score generation

---

## 📌 Summary

The results demonstrate the effectiveness of YOLOv8 for real-time helmet detection tasks. The trained model successfully learns discriminative visual features and performs reliably across a variety of traffic and riding scenarios.

This folder serves as a record of the model's training progress, evaluation metrics, and detection performance.
